data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['mænli]
*tính từ & phó từ
 ■có tính chất đàn ông; có đức tính đàn ông; hùng dũng, mạnh mẽ, can đảm, kiên cường
 ■có vẻ đàn ông (đàn bà)
 ■hợp với đàn ông (đồ dùng)

Anh - Anh
manly
■ adjective (manlier, manliest)
1》 having or denoting those good qualities traditionally associated with men, such as courage and strength.
2》 (of an activity) befitting a man.
Derivatives
manlinessnoun

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
manly
▸ adjective
1his manly physique: VIRILE, masculine, strong, all-male, muscular, muscly, strapping, well built, sturdy, robust, rugged, tough, powerful, brawny, red-blooded, vigorous; informal hunky.
2their manly deeds: BRAVE, courageous, bold, valiant, valorous, fearless, plucky, macho, manful, intrepid, daring, heroic, lionhearted, gallant, chivalrous, swashbuckling, adventurous, stout-hearted, dauntless, doughty, resolute, determined, stalwart; informal gutsy, spunky.
Opposites
effeminate, cowardly.
